duck: Biophysical chemistry - Biophysical chemistry is a relatively new branch of chemistry that covers a broad spectrum of research activities involving biological systems.
European Biophysical Societies' Association - The European Biophysics Journal is published by Springer Science+Business Media on behalf of the European Biophysical Societies Association.
Medical biophysics - Medical Biophysics refers to the domain of study that uses physics to describe or effect biological process for the purpose of medical application.
biophysics definition: a branch of science concerned with the application of physical principles and methods to biological problems.
Biophysics is an interdisciplinary science that uses the methods of, and theories from physics to study biological systems.
Outline of biophysics - Biophysics – interdisciplinary science that uses the methods of physics to study biological systems.
Biophysical Society - The Biophysical Society is an American scientific society that exists to encourage the development and dissemination of knowledge in biophysics.

wiki.text:
'Biophysics' is an interdisciplinary science that uses the methods of, and
theories from physics to study biological systems.<ref>[https://www.biophysics.-
org/Portals/1/PDFs/Career%20Center/Careers%20In%20Biophysics.pdf Careers in
Biophysics brochure, Biophysical Society]</ref> Biophysics spans all levels of
biological organization, from the molecular scale to whole organisms and
ecosystems. Biophysical research shares significant overlap with biochemistry,
nanotechnology, bioengineering, agrophysics, and systems biology. It has been
suggested as a bridge between biology and physics.
